# Keep README Up to Date

After completing any code changes, review whether the README.md needs to be updated.

## When to Update

- New features or functionality added
- Existing features modified or removed
- Configuration, setup steps, or dependencies changed
- API or usage instructions affected
- Project structure changed (new files/folders)

## When NOT to Update

- Pure refactors with no behavioral change
- Bug fixes that don't affect documented behavior
- Internal implementation details not mentioned in README

## Process

1. Read the current README.md
2. Compare against the changes just made
3. If any documented content is now outdated or incomplete, update the relevant sections
4. Keep the same style and structure as the existing README
